\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Liz:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> Liz felt excited to see her younger brother, as always. They shared a close, loving bond, and she missed him, having not seen him since early in the summer. Liz was particularly excited about this trip because she finally got to meet Sarah, the girl Evan called "the one."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 - Joe:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::2> Joe was hiding a secret. Although everyone knew that he was the one who had invited the mystery guest, they had no idea that it was Bridget, Evan and Liz's mom. Joe felt a little pumped and excited about his role in setting everything up. But he was even more excited about the secret that only he knew about, which would be revealed the next day - a proposal to Liz.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 Evan: }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::2>Evan was extremely excited. While he loved his sister, missed her, and looked forward to seeing her, his real excitement lay in introducing Sarah to Liz for the first time.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 Sarah:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> Sarah's emotional state was primarily neutral. She was not nervous about meeting Liz, but she had a busy workload she was itching to get back to. If it had been her choice, she would have stayed in Champaign and attended to her event coordinator duties. But Evan wanted to come home for a few days and introduce her to his sister. Sarah's primary motivation to join him had nothing to do with the holidays, but rather her feeling obligated to her boyfriend.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 However, she had decided to try to overcome all of her conflict and embrace the evening. At the beginning of the scene, she was reserved and a bit stiff, but as the night wore on, she couldn't help but be swallowed up by the warm and loving family known as the Vaughns.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf8 Bridget:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0  }{\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Bridget was thrilled to see her family on Christmas. Although she had promised to spend Christmas with her husband's family this year, she was able to get away for a short two-day trip at the behest and the expense of Liz's boyfriend Joe. To add to the fun and excitement, Bridget told Liz and Evan that she would be on a Christmas cruise, so they would not suspect that she was the mystery guest. Her being revealed as the mystery guest added to the incredible energy that was already present.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
